=begin

Input - array of strings
Output - array of strings

# explicit requirements
- for each substring, replace with a string with vowels removed
Implicit requirements
- return a new array 

Data structure 

use map to create a new array and gsub with regex to get rid of strings

High Level Algorithm

Create constant of vowels to check characters against

for each substring, create new substring but don't include vowels 
    # use gsub and a regex? 

pseudocode

str.gsub(/[aeiouAEIOU]/, ""))


p remove_vowels(['green', 'yellow', 'black', 'white']) == ['grn', 'yllw', 'blck', 'wht']
=end

def remove_vowels arr 
    arr.map { |color| color.gsub(/[aeiouAEIOU]/, "") }
end

p remove_vowels(['green', 'yellow', 'black', 'white']) == ['grn', 'yllw', 'blck', 'wht']